<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1437,680,886]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,788,814]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
I have examined the 
<typeStatus box="[566,678,788,814]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">holotypes</typeStatus>
, including the male genitalia, of 
<taxonomicName authority="(NMW)" baseAuthorityName="NMW" box="[1058,1345,788,815]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jenniferiduae">
<emphasis box="[1058,1244,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">H. jenniferiduae</emphasis>
(NMW)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(HMNH)" baseAuthorityName="HMNH" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zicsii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">H. zicsii</emphasis>
(HMNH)
</taxonomicName>
and conclude without doubt that they represent different species. The specimen imaged (
<figureCitation box="[1320,1402,824,851]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–35" captionStartId="69.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[171,1426,203,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-15@69.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="69" captionText="FIGURES 34–35. Habitus and male genitalia of holotypes. 34. Hydrochus compactus n. sp. 35. Hydrochus zicsii Makhan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5043318" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5043318/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) is the 
<typeStatus box="[192,294,860,886]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
